rComments: This is the hardest course I have taken in University thus far. I failed the midterm, while the average was a 50. Kevin is actually a decent professor but the course material is just too damn hard. Everything was counterintuitive to me, and I had to end up memorizing a lot in hopes of getting a decent grade. That didn't happen.

If you think this is a bird course, think again (at least it was until fall 2019). Kevin decided to boost up his difficulty apparently and the class average for the midterm was 51%. I'm pretty scared about the final now, and plus he refused to curve the midterm, said "if the overall is not a B- I'll consider curving". Lectures are great thou.
Amazing prof. Genuinely cares about his students. Explains stuff clearly and thoroughly.

He explains concepts thoroughly and makes class super interesting. If you skip class you can still figure the material out from his slides and problem sets which are SUPER easy . So long as you do practice questions and problem sets you'll be all set for the midterm and final

Took his class when he first taught the course last year fall semester and felt his exams were pretty fair. Make sure you carefully study the problem sets and understand the solutions while going over the lecture slides. MC questions can be quite tricky since it's very conceptual based but written questions are similar to problem sets from class.
